        <div class="offset1 span5">
          <h1>Five blocks.</h1>
          <p>Macon’s Five By Five program is a simple idea: take five blocks in a blighted neighborhood of town and use every city department and willing volunteer to help clean up the area in a five week period.</p>
          <p>From mowing public property, to installing smoke detectors, fixing potholes, meeting with neighborhood groups, boarding up vacant housing, repairing broken street lights, and sweeping streets, all work is done within the city budget.</p>
          <p>Much of the focus in the five weeks is put on establishing connections with those in the neighborhood. Sustainability within the area is key, and can only be done by reaching out with community partners such as church groups and local leaders.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="span5">
          <img src="/img/blocks.png" alt="Five blocks" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Weeks -->
