        <div class="offset1 span5">
          <h1>Five weeks.</h1>
          <p>After the five weeks, another area within a different ward will be targeted. Since Macon is comprised of five total wards, it takes approximately 6 months before the same ward is targeted again. From the time the Five By Five plan started in early November and ended in December, over <a href="http://www.macon.com/2011/12/19/1829981/first-five-block-project-ends.html">18,000 pounds of debris</a> had been cleared from the original test area in Ward 1.</p>
          <p>And, while Macon city employees can help patch roads, trim overhanging trees, and clean gutters and right-of-ways, it’s up to residents and volunteers in the community to help clear debris from private property and empty lots. According to Laura Jackson, Program Coordinator at <a href="http://www.kmbbc.org/">Keep Macon-Bibb Beautiful</a>, over 350 volunteers showed up during the course of the first Five By Five.</p>
        </div>

